This paper deals with deep learning methods applied to natural language processing and knowledge representation, which are typically covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on unsupervised learning techniques for building a unified conceptual framework, which is a common theme in these sub-fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
